args: Er, sorry. I didn't realize I was\nso hungry.
Well, it IS lunchtime. I could use some\nfood myself.
That hut appears to serve foods.\nShall we go see what they offer?
Oh my! I wasn't expecting such a crowd.
Hey, I been waitin' ages here!\nWhere's my order?!
The line just keeps growing...\nI can't keep up on my own!
If I just had a couple more sets\nof hands, I'd be golden.
Well, if it isn't my favorite customer!\nWhat brings you to—
Wait a second Nina, now's not the time for\nglad-handing!
Excuse me, could I please have some\ntropical punch?
Looks like you're stretched a bit thin.\nDo you want a hand?
Well all righty. That means you're on\ncustomer service with me, Prince!
Whew... Restaurant work is no joke.
Don't cry. I'll help you find her.
He won't stop... What should I do?
I've been helping Nina out at\nthe restaurant.
Wait, really? Did you happen to see\nthis boy's mother?
Hmm... I didn't see anyone looking for a\nlost child, at least.
If I could just get him to stop crying,\nI'd ask him what his mother looks like—\nbut I can't even manage that much.
I'm honestly at a bit of a loss here.
Hmm... Wait, I have an idea!
Here you are. One summer parfait.
Holy moly, this looks good as HECK!
Children love sweets; it's one of life's\nfew constants.
And besides, good food always brings\na smile.
Thank you, Cleo. He might actually talk\nto me now.
THERE you are! I've been looking\neverywhere for you!
Mommy, look! The nice lady made me\nthis super tasty parfait!
Oh my! Thank you all so much.
We're just happy you two were reunited.
Me too; thank you both for your help.\nNow, I have to get back to my rounds.
We should return to our duties as well.\nBusiness doesn't seem to have slowed\nin the slightest.
Well, if it isn't {player_name}!\nHelping out, are you?
Good for you! Customer service is great\nendurance training—though not everyone\nsurvives it.
I commend you putting your life on the\nline for the sake of your training!
Er, thanks. Anyway, what can I get you?
There's only one thing worth drinking after\na rigorous training session, and that's a\nfresh algae slime and liver shake!
Ha ha!\n...Wait, is that a real thing!

You mix some slime with a few medicinal
herbs, a nice chunk of liver, and a few
other bits and bobs, and voila—one big,
gloopy nutrition drink!
The healthiest things often do.\nOne must simply consider it\npart of their training!
Well, either way, I'm pretty sure we don't\nhave that on the menu...
I have all the ingredients here, so I don't\nsee why not. Just a moment.
YES! Now for a taste test...
Wow, Cleo. You may have just set\na new standard for nutrition drinks.\nIt's so delightfully gloopy!
*sniff* *sniff* What's that?\nDo I smell a quitter?
*sigh* All right, all right—but just a bit.\n...Wow, this actually isn't half bad.
But of course.\nI've made better meals with less.
Heh. You never cease to amaze me, Cleo.
Whew! I think we can finally take\na breather.
Guys, seriously, thank you SO much for\nyour help. I would've been eaten alive\nwithout you.
I think Cleo took the brunt of it.
Not at all. You were equally busy, if not\nmore so.
...Right. Didn't we come here originally\nbecause we were hungry? I totally forgot.
That's no surprise. We've barely had a\nmoment to breathe.
After all you've done, the least I can do\nis feed you. On the house, of course!
I would be happy to help with the cooking.
No, you rest. I'm not about to make you\ncook your own thank-you meal!
By the way, that swimsuit of yours was a\nreal hit with the customers, Cleo.
Why else do you think we stayed so busy?\nHee hee!
I did notice a spike in customers after we\nstarted helping...
I-I refuse to believe I had any part in that.\nIt was purely coincidence.
At the very least, everyone seemed to\nreally enjoy the food you were serving.
I can't speak to how your outfit affected\nthe customer count, but it definitely didn't\naffect your talent as a chef.
Of course not. My abilities could never\nbe hindered by something so trivial.
Now, I believe we can put this topic\nto rest.
Actually, I did hear one customer say\nthe cook in the swimsuit was cute.\nThey had a point, too.
...Can I take that to mean you're of\nthe same opinion?
Oh, that swimsuit is definitely cute.\nNo doubt.
Here you go! ...What's up, Cleo?\nYou're red as a beet.
